mode, `generateMetadata`\\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:171:to be produced by `generateMetadata`.\\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:286:Sequencing with `generateMetadata`, native-test verification, codex fixup,\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTaskTests.java:47:        TestGenerateMetadataTask task = registerGenerateMetadataTask(project, \\\"generateMetadata\\\", coordinates);\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTaskTests.java:76:        TestGenerateMetadataTask task = registerGenerateMetadataTask(project, \\\"generateMetadata\\\", coordinates);\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTaskTests.java:92:        TestGenerateMetadataTask task = registerGenerateMetadataTask(project, \\\"generateMetadata\\\", coordinates);\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_60\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The repo’s documented first step for native-test verification is `generateMetadata --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar`, not manual editing. Since tracing support is unavailable in the current GraalVM, I’m trying that supported generation path first to produce the baseline `reachability-metadata.json`, then I’ll verify whether native tests still need a hand patch.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_61\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '85,135p' forge/docs/native-test-verification.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_62\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '40,90p' docs/CONTRIBUTING.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_62\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '40,90p' docs/CONTRIBUTING.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"- ask you if you want to create a pull request, or you want to keep working on it locally\\n\\nIf you already have the test project structure in this repository and need to generate or regenerate metadata, use the `generateMetadata` task:\\n\\n```shell\\n./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0\\n```\\n\\nTo change the user-code-filter used during collection, pass `--agentAllowedPackages` with a comma-separated list of packages or `fromJar` to derive package roots from the resolved library JAR:\\n\\n```shell\\n./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\\n./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=com.example.pkg,org.acme.lib\\n```\\n\\n### Checklist\\nIn order to ensure that all contributions follow the same standards of quality we have devised a following list of requirements for each new added library.\\n`org.example:library` project is also included as a template for new libraries.\\n\\n* GraalVM Reachability Metadata in this repo only contains JSON files as described\\nin [Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration)\\nsection of the Native Image documentation.\\n* All other library tweaks (such as build time initialization through `native-image.properties`) must not be included\\nhere. By default, it should be assumed that all user libraries are runtime initialized. Build-time initialization can\\nnot be included as it does not compose and can break code in unpredictable ways.\\n* Make sure that you are using [Conditional Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/#specifying-reflection-metadata-in-json)\\nin order to precisely define the metadata scope. This is a hard requirement as it prevents unnecessary bloating of\\nimages.\\n* Once you want to create a pull request, you will be asked to fill out the [following list](../.github/pull_request_template.md).\\n\\nℹ️ To learn more about collecting metadata, see [How To Collect Metadata](CollectingMetadata.md).\\n\\n### Generate Metadata and Test\\n\\nUse the `scaffold` task to generate metadata and test stubs:\\n\\n```bash\\n./gradlew scaffold --coordinates com.example:my-library:1.0.0\\n```\\n\\nYou can now run\\n\\n```bash\\n./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0\\n```\\n\\nto execute the tests.\\n\\nIt's expected that they fail, because the scaffold task only generated a stub which you need to implement.\\n\\n### Metadata structure\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_61\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '85,135p' forge/docs/native-test-verification.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"  produced 172 and were folded into the running `metadataConfigDirs`.\\n- `intervention_records` — ordered list of `{stage, kind: \\\"codex\\\",\\n  log_path}` entries (zero or one entry; codex is invoked at most once\\n  per gate invocation).\\n\\n## 4. Loop\\n\\n```mermaid\\nflowchart TD\\n    Start([invoke gate]) --> Init[reset output_dir + runs_dir<br/>config_dirs = []<br/>i = 0]\\n    Init --> Agent[gradlew generateMetadata<br/>--agentAllowedPackages=fromJar]\\n    Agent -- fail --> Outer{i &lt; max-native-test-verification-iterations?}\\n    Agent -- pass --> Test[gradlew test<br/>-Pcoordinates=&lt;g:a:v&gt;]\\n    Test -- pass --> PassAgent([return PASSED])\\n    Test -- fails before nativeTest --> Codex\\n    Test -- nativeTest fails --> Outer\\n    Outer -- no --> Codex\\n    Outer -- yes --> Run[gradlew runNativeTraceImage<br/>-PtraceMetadataPath=runs/cycle-i<br/>-PtraceMetadataConditionPackages=&lt;packages&gt;<br/>-PmetadataConfigDirs=&lt;config_dirs&gt;]\\n    Run --> Route{binary exit code}\\n    Route -- 0